\begin_layout Standard
So, the very first thing we want to do is to pick a simple case, and explore
 it in the most concrete, direct way possible.
 It seems that this would be to write down spin connections at the event
 horizon of a Swarzschild BH.
 The obvious choice of coordinates is to pick infalling frames, slap vierbeins
 on that, and then write down spinors in the vierbein frame.
 Sounds easy enough.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Two charts are needed to cover the sphere.
 There's only one way to stitch them together, for the space coords.
 However, there seem to be two ways to glue gamma matrices to the vierbeins,
 +1 and -1 for the (Dirac) gamma matrices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Are there any non-trivial topological maps, twists between the vierbein
 field and the spin complex, besides, this ambiguity about gluing the center
 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ +1,-1\right\} $
